com.adobe.aemforms.fm.model

Class FormOptions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.adobe.aemforms.fm.model.FormOptions
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    AFFOptions, AFOptions

    public class FormOptions
extends Object
    FormOptions represents the common configurable properties that will be honored while creating a Form through FormGenerationService.

      • setFormLocation

        public void setFormLocation(String formLocation)
        Set the repository path of the directory where form will be created. If this value is not set or is invalid, the form will be created in the directory where the Form Template reference resides.
        Parameters:
        formLocation - String representing a valid repository path of a directory that will contain the form.

        public void setName(String name)
        Set the name of the form. If characters other than alphabets, numbers, hyphens and underscores are specified, will be replaced by hyphens.If not set, will be generated based on the Form Template name.
        Parameters:
        name - String representing the name of the form.
